<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - FAN SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Horton Fan With
        Cummins ISM With or Without Air Conditioning
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Horton Fan With Cummins ISM With or Without Air Conditioning</title>
        <table id="t0827502" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Horton Fan With Cummins ISM With or Without Air Conditioning</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.61in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.64in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.67in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.43in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect 31-way interface connector (957) and A/C pressure switch connector (240).
                                Measure resistance between (957) terminal 18 and (240) circuit 23-GB.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(957), term. 18 and (240), 23-GB.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23-GB.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Does vehicle have air conditioning?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 4.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (240) measure resistance across black wires of A/C pressure switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Switch (240), black wire to black wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective A/C pressure switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (240) measure resistance from black wire to black wire of A/C pressure switch
                                jumper plug.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Jumper plug (240), black wire to black wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective A/C jumper plug.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance from (957) cavity 17 and connector (240) circuit 23C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(957), cavity 17 and (240), 23C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23C, conn. (957) or air conditioning input
                                circuit, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (957) and (240), disconnect connector (239), and start engine.
                                <emph type="bold">WARNING: Fan will be rotating.</emph>
                                At connector (239) and circuit 23D, measure voltage to ground.
                                <emph type="bold">NOTE: Engine must be cool and when applicable, A/C should be turned
                                    off.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(239), 23D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in fan clutch driver circuit, or circuit 23D from
                                interface connector (957), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With engine still running and relatively cool, at connector (239), measure voltage
                                from circuit 23D to 23-GA.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(239), 23D to 23-GA.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23-GA, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With engine still running and relatively cool, reconnect fan solenoid connector (239).
                                Does fan slow or stop rotating?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace defective fan solenoid.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Shut off engine. Fan circuits check good. If fan fails to function properly, check ECM
                                programming and A/C pressure switch opening pressure.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
